text:
Tornier's frog, Tornier's Australian tree frog or black-shinned rocket frog ("Litoria tornieri") is a frog from northern Australia. It lives in Western Australia, the Northern Territory, and Queensland.
This frog lives in many different kinds of places, especially temporary bodies of water that dry up.
This frog lays eggs on the surface of the water. Tadpoles take 6-7 weeks to become frogs.
